1) check when did the system last reboot
$ uptime   - <curr_time> up <time since last boot> .....
OR
$ last reboot
($ who -b is least preffered)

2) open Image Viewer and default programs:
$ eog <image_path>     # opens Image Viewer
$ xdg-open <file_path> # open file with default program

3) Hard Disks and mounts
gui for disks is at <Win-Key>-a  open disks
select the required disk - select the required partition
you can fix the Read-only premission using this gui
Auto mount (at FS startup) go to Cog-wheel-icon -> Edit Mount option ->
        -> user session Defaults to OFF

4) Ubuntu defaults: 
    a) set the x-terminal sym link to point there (system wide confing)
    $ sudo update-alternatives --config x-terminal-emulator
    ==> then choose the selection number of the desired terminal, and enter
    OR
    b) set gnome to be default
    gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.default-applications.terminal exec 'gnome-terminal'

5) Resize and move
    Alt-F7 : then move by cursor or mouse
    Alt+F8 : them resize by cursor or mouse

6) Network problems
to connect (raise) one on the network cards
$ ifconfig -a
$ ifconfig <name> down / up
exmple : raise the ethernet cable card
ifconfig enp60s0 up

